### GET /api/recipes

This endpoint retrieves a list of recipes.

#### Request

No request body is required for this GET request.

##### Headers

No specific headers are required for this request.

##### Authorization

No authorization is required for this request.

#### Response

The response for this request is a list of recipes in JSON format.

##### Body

The response body contains an array of recipe objects, where each recipe object has the following properties:

- `recipeId` (string)

- `name` (string)

- `description` (string)

- `ingredients` (array of strings)

- `instructions` (string)


Example response body:

``` json
[
  {
    "recipeId": "string",
    "name": "string",
    "description": "string",
    "ingredients": ["string1", "string2"],
    "instructions": "string"
  },
  {
    "recipeId": "string",
    "name": "string",
    "description": "string",
    "ingredients": ["string1", "string2"],
    "instructions": "string"
  }
]

 ```

The response schema for the list of recipes can be defined as follows:

``` json
{
  "type": "array",
  "items": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "recipeId": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "name": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "description": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "ingredients": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "instructions": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```
